ree structures with AST analysis capabilities.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install tree-interval\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```python\nfrom tree_interval import Tree, Leaf, Position\n\n# Create a basic tree\ntree = Tree(\"Example\")\nroot = Leaf(Position(0, 100, \"Root\"))\nchild = Leaf(Position(10, 50, \"Child\"))\n\ntree.root = root\ntree.add_leaf(child)\n\n# Visualize the tree\ntree.visualize()\n```\n\n## Repository Links\n- GitHub: [https://github.com/kairos-xx/tree-interval](https://github.com/kairos-xx/tree-interval)\n- PyPI: [https://pypi.org/project/tree-interval/](https://pypi.org/project/tree-interval/)\n\n## Features\n- Tree structure management with position tracking\n- AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) analysis\n- Frame analysis for runtime code inspection\n- Position-aware node tracking\n- Customizable tree visualization\n- JSON serialization/deserialization\n\n## License\nMIT License - See LICENSE file for details\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tree_interval.visualizer", "documentation": ["Visualizer module for tree interval package."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "tree_interval.visualizer.DEFAULT_CONFIG", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "tree_interval.visualizer.TreeVisualizer", "xref": {"fqname": "tree_interval.visualizer.visualizer.TreeVisualizer", "project": null}}, {"name": "tree_interval.visualizer.VisualizationConfig", "xref": {"fqname": "tree_interval.visualizer.visualizer.VisualizationConfig", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "tree_interval.visualizer.config", "documentation": ["Configuration for tree visualization."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tree_interval.visualizer.config.VisualizationConfig", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "tree_interval.visualizer.config.VisualizationConfig.show_info", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tree_interval.visual